{
  "texts": [
    "Of these, 24 were from the literature review, 22 from expert crowdsourcing, and 11 from targeted searches.",
    "Two of the final tools were commercial in nature and not published academically, while the remaining 55 had an associated preprint or peer-reviewed publication.",
    "These 57 tools were then assessed in full.",
    "Our structured approach to selection was time-consuming and we could not always review all available information.",
    "The tools in each category were diverse, the quality of documentation varied, and while researchers were assigned to the categories with which they were most familiar, they could not be familiar with all sub-areas of multiple categories."
  ]
}